    "body": "### Problem\n\nError index out of bound appears when removing characters on the last row in insert mode while using copilot with inline completion enabled.\nI am using configuration for copilot from [nvim-lspconfig](https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/blob/master/lsp/copilot.lua).\n\nError:\n```\nError in CursorMovedI Autocommands for \"*\":\nLua callback: ...cal/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/inline_completion.lua:223: Index out of bounds\nstack traceback:\n        [C]: in function 'nvim_buf_get_lines'\n        ...cal/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/inline_completion.lua:223: in function 'show'\n        ...cal/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/inline_completion.lua:296: in function 'automatic_request'\n        ...cal/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/inline_completion.lua:80: in function <...cal/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/inline_completion.lua:79>\n```\n\n### Steps to reproduce using \"nvim -u minimal_init.lua\"\n\n1. [minimal_init.lua](https://gist.github.com/danbulgar/d025e3cadeb68052ba6817cd4aab8010#file-minimal_init-lua) is just a config from nvim-lspconfig and inline completion enabled. Copy its content to `minimal_init.lua`.\n2. Install [copilot-language-server](https://github.com/github/copilot-language-server-release).\n2. Open a file using `nvim --clean -u minimal_init.lua`, for example `nvim --clean -u minimal_init.lua minimal_init.lua`.\n3. Go to last line, remove all characters, in insert mode press backspace to move to the previous line.\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nExpected to move to previous line without error.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.0-dev-1329+ga053186a\n\n### Language server name/version\n\ncopilot-language-server 1.378.0\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nWSL 2 / Ubuntu 24.04.2\n\n### Log file\n\n_No response_",
